<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>be in a flutter • have a flutter</xh5><p> <i>be in a flutter—</i>1. <i>(also: be all of a flutter)</i> be in a very nervous, confused, or excited state: The concert is coming soon. <u>I’m in a flutter</u>. 2. <i>(of a room, etc.)</i> be in a disordered or untidy state: Let me never see this room <u>in a flutter</u> again.</p><p> <i>have a flutter</i>—(coll.) gamble on a small scale: The opportunities of the share market were open.... Men and youths, women and maidens, all could <u>have a “flutter</u>.”</p> </entry>
